name.en: Block Storage for Virtual Machines

description.en:
Enterprise Grade Block Storage made simple.

We provide up to 15 TiB of Block Storage options you can add to every of your Virtual Machines.

You can configure pay-per-use Virtual Disks (vDisks) with flexible size from 5 GiB to 1 TiB per Volume, dedicated to each Virtual Machine.


Performance Storage

Intended for Applications requiring fast response time for less critical business revenue.

Typical Applications: Virtualization, Business applications, such as SAP®, Oracle®.

Technical Specifications: RAID 50 block-level striping with distributed parity, up to 57K IOPS at 8K random IOs with 80/20 read/write ratio with less than or equal to 25 milliseconds response time.

name.en: Block Storage for Physical Servers

description.en:
Enterprise Grade Block Storage that meets all your needs.

We provide a variety of reliable performance options and fully flexible capacity you can share across all your workloads.

You can configure pay-per-use LUN sizes in 1 GiB increments from 1GiB to 8TiB, and pay-as-you-grow them in any 1 GiB increments at any time.


High Performance Storage

Intended for Write intensive applications, and applications that are critical to business revenue and require high performance and availability.

Typical Applications: SAP®, Oracle® Business Intelligence and more.

Technical Specifications: RAID 10 mirrored sets in a striped set with fault tolerance, up to 80K IOPS at 8K random IOs with 80/20 read/write ratio, with less than 25 milliseconds response time.


Performance Storage

Intended for Applications requiring fast response time for less critical business revenue.

Typical Applications: Business applications, such as SAP®, Oracle®.

Technical Specifications: RAID 50 block-level striping with distributed parity, up to 57K IOPS at 8K random IOs with 80/20 read/write ratio with less than or equal to 25 milliseconds response time.


Bulk Storage

Intended for less important applications, such as applications requiring slower response time for less business critical revenue.

Typical Applications: Content Depot, Fixed Content, Compliance, Long Term Retention, or Compute intensive applications requiring SAN storage.

Technical Specifications: RAID 60 straight block-level striping of RAID 0 with the distributed double parity of RAID 6, up to 10K IOPS at 8K random IOs with 80/20 read/write ratio with less than or equal to 30 milliseconds response time.

name.en: Microsoft® Hyper-V Microsoft® Windows Virtual Machine

description.en:
Enterprise Grade Microsoft® Hyper-V Virtual Machines from HPE, your Global Certified Microsoft® Service Provider.

We provide a full range of 12 Virtual Machine vCPU and RAM preset combinations to meet your needs, up to 16 vCPU and 64GB RAM.

Virtual Machines are hosted on shared Multi-Tenant Certified Microsoft® Hyper-V Hypervisor Hosts and underpinning hardware managed by HPE at all times.


You can choose to administer each Server yourself, or HPE can administer it for you, and with the following options:


You administer the Server:

Servers you administer must reside on a Virtual Datacenter VLAN you administer.

HPE provides certified standard Microsoft® Windows Server® Operating System Licenses. The Server and Microsoft® Windows Server® Operating System are installed by HPE.

Servers you administer are not monitored, patched or security-checked by HPE, all system administration, monitoring and instrumentation to manage the Servers is under your full control and responsibility. HPE has no access to Servers you administer.

HPE Backup and Recovery Services are optionally available and can be added at any time to your existing Virtual Machines, providing you install HPE Backup Agents when requesting the service.


HPE administers the Server:

Servers administered by HPE must reside on a Virtual Datacenter VLAN administered by HPE.

HPE provides certified standard Microsoft® Windows Server® Operating System Licenses. The Server and Microsoft® Windows Server® Operating System are installed by HPE.

HPE maintains administrative access at all times and is accountable for all management, monitoring, patching and security of Microsoft® Windows Server® and associated Hardware.

HPE Provides McAfee® Anti-malware protection for Windows® in addition to Systems Management, including Change, Incident, and Problem Management.

HPE Backup and Recovery Services are optionally available and can be added at any time to your existing Virtual Machines.

name.en: Provision SAP Standalone Component

description.en:
Imagine if you could improve SAP® application provisioning time, gain flexibility to add capacity without capital expenditures, and support additional demand and lower overall costs

HPE Helion Business Applications for SAP® provide you with agility, flexibility, improved cost control, and service levels required to meet the dynamic requirements facing CIOs.
A Cloud hosting model can provide these things, but you may be hesitant to move your ERP applications to the cloud due to security and data control concerns. HPE solves these obstacles by providing the most secured cloud infrastructure in the industry and providing management tools to allow you to continuously manage your SAP® applications.
 
HPE Helion Managed Virtual Private Cloud SAP® services provides you with an SAP® application environment running on HP Enterprise owned infrastructure, operated and housed in a HP Enterprise Datacenter, with logical access to the application environment provided over the Managed Virtual Private Cloud connectivity solution defined when setting up your one or more Virtual Datacenters. The service provides all Infrastructure and SAP® Basis Management for the Application including end to end operation of the Virtual Datacenter LAN, Operating System instance, Database, SAP® Basis Instances.

HPE As a Service Solution for SAP HANA provides HANA management services for both customer provided appliances and HPE HANA infrastructure that enables a flexible and scalable alternative to deploying HANA with faster deployment times and minimal capital expenditure. Setting up and running SAP HANA requires specialized skills and expertise of HANA appliances, software, and hardware elements. HPE As a Service Solution for SAP HANA combines proven methods, tools, and frameworks—implemented by experienced HPE SAP applications and cloud consultants.
HPE is certified by SAP® as a global provider of cloud services in support of SAP® solutions. Global availability of data centers delivers enterprise cloud services to provision SAP® applications. Modular infrastructure and cloud services avoid service lock in. Industry-leading security architecture—seven levels of security address all aspects of a client’s security requirement.

The Managed Virtual Private Cloud for SAP® and HANA management services covers activities and tasks that include:
. SAP® Basis operations
. SAP® Basis administration
. SAP® Basis security management
. SAP® Database and SAP® HANA administration and security
. SAP® Server administration
. Backup and Restore management
. SAN Management for the SAP® Basis Operations Service
. SAP® Database and HANA Server system maintenance
. Proactive monitoring, event detection and notification (availability, capacity and performance)
